	<content:encoded><![CDATA[<span style="color: #29303b; font-family: Georgia; font-size: 13px;"><div style="text-align: justify;">
<span style="font-size: 16px;">Interview answer from Ezra Zygmuntowicz to a question posed by Yours Truly...</span><br />
</div>
<p /><blockquote style="font-style: italic; line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 0.6em; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 32px; padding-right: 32px; padding-top: 0px;">
<p /><p />
<span style="color: #29303b; font-family: Georgia; font-size: 12px;" /><blockquote style="font-style: italic; line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 0.6em; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 32px; padding-right: 32px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: left;">
<strong style="margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px;"><span style="color: #cc3333; font-family: Georgia; font-style: italic; line-height: 19px;"><span style="color: #29303b; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"></span><span style="font-size: 16px;">Victor Goff, USA&gt;&gt;</span></span></strong><span style="color: #cc3333; font-family: Georgia; font-style: italic; font-weight: bold; line-height: 19px;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"> How do you see the market for Ruby Programmers in the work place, and do you see it as primarily tied to Rails and Web related work? Do you see trends in administration or other work? What’s the future for Ruby?</span></span>
</blockquote></blockquote></span>

<div style="color: #29303b; font-family: Georgia; font-size: 12px;"><div style="color: black; font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 14px;"><div style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 12px; line-height: 19px;" /><div style="line-height: 1.5em; margin-bottom: 0.6em; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: justify;"><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: normal; line-height: 22px;"><strong style="margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px;">Ezra&gt;&gt;</strong> <em style="margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px;">I see a huge demand for Ruby programmers and not near enough supply of good developers</em>. Of course folks are always hiring for Rails web developers but I also see lots of jobs for Ruby that are not web related. Ruby is being used more and more as enterprise glue language and I think it really shines in that space.</span></span></div><br /></div></div>
<p />
<div style="line-height: 1.5em; margin-bottom: 0.6em; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;"><span style="color: #29303b; font-family: Georgia; font-size: 13px; line-height: normal;">See the rest of the interview at the link above!</span><br /></span></div></div><div class="blogger-post-footer"><img class="posterous_download_image" src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/2949792777916502048-1289050890093606464?l=vgoff.blogspot.com" height="1" alt="" width="1" /></div>]]></content:encoded>
